# Python Development Standards

Apply these conventions when generating or modifying Python code.

---

## Code style

Follow PEP 8. Enforce with `ruff` (preferred over flake8 + isort + black).

```toml
# pyproject.toml
[tool.ruff]
line-length = 88
target-version = "py39"
select = ["E", "F", "I", "N", "S", "UP"]

[tool.ruff.isort]
known-first-party = ["myproject"]
```

### Import order

```python
# 1 — stdlib
import os
from pathlib import Path
from typing import Optional

# 2 — third-party
import requests
from pydantic import BaseModel

# 3 — local
from .models import User
from ..config import settings
```

### Type annotations

Use type hints on all public functions and class methods:

```python
def create_user(name: str, email: str, age: Optional[int] = None) -> User:
    ...
```

Use `from __future__ import annotations` on Python < 3.10 to avoid forward-reference issues.

